'''Low Level Alchemy''' (or ''low alch/low alching'') is a [[standard spellbook]] [[spell]] that turns alchemisable items into [[coins]] at 40% of the specialty shop sale price, equivalent to [[general store]] buying prices. This is about 2/3 of [[High Level Alchemy]] value, which turns items into coins worth 60% of the item's sale price.

This spell requires 21 [[Magic]], using 1 [[nature rune]] and 3 [[fire rune]]s. It can be cast for free 30 times per day with the [[Explorer's ring]], though no experience is gained. Low Level Alchemy is not recommended for Magic training or for profit as the coins gained are rarely greater than the cost of the item and spell. This spell costs the same as High Level Alchemy if using an item that provides unlimited [[fire rune]]s. It yields less [[experience]] per cast and per hour even though the casting speed of this spell is 40% faster.

When in the [[Alchemist's Playground]] of [[Mage Training Arena]], Low Level Alchemy can only be cast every five ticks instead of the usual three.

Casting this spell at the [[Fountain of Rune]] is a requirement for the [[Easy Wilderness Diary]].
